1.title: Shut Up! How Much?
1.plot: The women of a family run resale company know as Women's Closet Exchange hope to launch a major "Handbag It Over" event without a hitch. However, some purse strings are attached.

2.title: 5 Finger Discount
2.plot: As store items begin to go missing, the resale women teach their staff about "Shoplift Prevention". Meanwhile, Laura attempts to find the perfect dress for a Grammy Awards attendee.

3.title: VIP: Very Important Purchasers
3.plot: The ladies plan a re-launch of their VIP Club, putting Jourdan and Jojo at odds over the finishing touches. Meanwhile, Molly attends her first closet buy for a fabulous corporate executive.

4.title: All About Who You Zoe
4.plot: The ladies run into old friend Rachel Zoe during New York Fashion Week. There they attend Mara Hoffman's fashion show and shop directly in Lela Rose's closet.

5.title: All Trunk, No Junk
5.plot: A socialite hosts a trunk show to help get the WCE name out to her elite circle of friends. Dena goes on her first closet buy, where a plastic surgeon built a new home to accommodate her closet.

6.title: Dressed Like a McQueen
6.plot: Sue and Diana attend an Alexander McQueen exhibit, while Laura and Meghan plan a "Mix & Match" event at a downtown co-op where they show consumers how resale items can complement retail items.

7.title: Size Does Matter
7.plot: The ladies hope to expand their brand by bringing in a visual merchandising specialist. Sue leaves Laura with a Town & Style magazine reporter, while she and Diana shop the closet of a local boutique.

8.title: Still Haute at 25
8.plot: A 25th anniversary sale is held; and Sue is surprised with a party to celebrate the occasion.

9.title: In Laura We Trust
9.plot: Laura puts the company's first off-site fashion show in jeopardy. Meanwhile, the ladies explore space possibilities for a new store, and meet a mother and daughter who have three closet buys in one.

10.title: Spring Forward, Vault Back
10.plot: The store's annual spring fashion show is held.

imdb.plot outline: Resale Royalty is a workplace documentary series set in St. Louis that follows Sue McCarthy along with her daughters, Diana and Laura, who own and operate one of the top resale stores in the country. This mother-daughter trio work to bring designer brands at affordable prices to their fashion savvy clientèle. With more than 25 years of experience in the resale business, Sue has big plans for the future, but she'll need her daughters, Diana and Laura, to help manage the expanding empire. However, mixing family and business is never easy as their differing personalities will put their business relationships to the test. From spectacular closet buys of posh St. Louis socialites to exclusive shopping tours across the country, "Resale Royalty" is an exploration of high-end fashion events, insider trends, designer insight and the highs-and-lows associated with a demanding business overseen by an eccentric staff, who are also family.
